% PHP Language Ontology - CNL Format
% Extends oo_ontology.cnl with PHP-specific concepts

% File/Module types
Every php-compilation-unit is a compilation-unit.
Every php-namespace is a namespace.

% Type definitions
Every php-class is a class.
Every php-interface is an interface.
Every php-trait is a trait.
Every php-enum is an enum.

% Members
Every php-method is a method.
Every php-function is a function.
Every php-field is a field.
Every php-property is a property.
Every php-constructor is a constructor.
Every php-constant is a field.

% Parameters
Every php-parameter is a parameter.

% Import
Every php-use is an import.
Every php-require is an import.
Every php-include is an import.

% Exception handling
Every php-try-block is a try-block.
Every php-catch-clause is a catch-clause.
Every php-finally-clause is a finally-clause.
Every php-throw-statement is a throw-statement.

% Control flow
Every php-return-statement is a return-statement.

% Other
Every php-variable is a variable.
Every php-reference is a reference.
Every php-attribute is an attribute.
Every php-anonymous-function is an anonymous-function.

% PHP-Specific Concepts
Every abstract-class is a class.
Every final-class is a class.
Every readonly-class is a class.

% Access Modifiers
Every public-member is a member.
Every private-member is a member.
Every protected-member is a member.

% Code Smells
Every php-god-class is a god-class.
Every php-long-method is a long-method.
